<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Factions</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Wrex">Wrex</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:51 p.m. 16/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Factions<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1503" TARGET=_self>Do factions actually work like they should?</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>No, the factions work, but they may take a while. An ogre was able to walk and perform transactions in any town that opposed ogres. It took him a long time of concentrated effort to do so however. He was 10th level minimum (not on a PvP server) when he was able to do it AND he focused on changing his faction. Another big consideration is what diety you initially choose. Necro's are restricted to evil gods, which usually doesn't bode well with many good NPCs.

<P>I believe factions are designed to be something you just can turn on and off from a few hours of work.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
